commands :
pwd-Present working directory
ls-list files
    ls -lah ==> List all files (including hidden files) with detailed information and readable sizes.
               -l long format
               -a All files includes hidden files
                -h  Human readable sizes
cd -change directory
mk dir <directory_name> ->creates directory
touch <file_name> ->creates files
cp -> copy file  or folders EX:cp notes.txt sheet.txt
mv -> move or rename files or folders
rm -> delete 
  rm -f<file name> ==> delete files  
  rm -rf<folder_name> ==>delete folders
tree -->displays structure 
to install tree use:
sudo apt install tree
